Use the standard library
This is how to filter_by_prefix of strings and prefix:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that n is strings's length
   Remember that m is prefix's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that s is item i in strings
      Remember that ok is 1
      When s's length is less than m, then:
         Remember that ok is 0
      But, if not:
         Remember that j is 0
         Do this m times:
            When item j in s is not item j in prefix, then:
               Remember that ok is 0
            End when
            Increase j
         End do
      End when
      When ok is 1, then:
         Add result to s
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know